1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 Bc5 {In the classical Ruy Lopez, black ignore whites 
pawn for the time being and focuses on development.} 4. O-O Nf6 {Black should 
have defended the pawn probably.} 5. Nxe5 Nxe5 6. d4 Bd6 7. dxe5 Bxe5 {White 
will try to utilize his kingside pawn advantage, attacking there.} 8. f4 {The 
bishop has only one safe square, and then comes the fork.} Bd6 9. e5 Bc5+ {Black 
uses a check to get out of the fork.} 10. Kh1 Ng8 {but the only safe square for 
the knight is back at home...} 11. Nc3 f5 12. Rb1 {preparing b4} c6 13. Bc4 Qh4 
14. b4 *

