1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 d6 4. d4 Bg4 {Not enjoying the pinned knight on c6, 
black returns the favor.} 5. dxe5 Bxf3 6. Qxf3 dxe5 7. Bxc6+ bxc6 {This 
variation works out better for white, who gets to recapture with the queen and 
preserve a healthier pawn structure, where as black is forced to take back with 
b-pawn.} 8. O-O {White has a nice lead in development.} Nf6 9. Qc3 Qd6 10. Nd2 
Qc5 11. Nc4 Bd6 12. Qd3 Rd8 13. Be3 *

