1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 d6 4. d4 Bd7 5. d5 Nce7 6. Bxd7+ Qxd7 7. c4 Nf6 8. 
Nc3 Qg4 {This looks scary. But white is fine.} 9. c5 Qxg2 {Black grabs the pawn 
and threatens to take the rook.} 10. Rg1 Qh3 {only option.} 11. Nb5 {Obviously 
threatening Nxc7+} Rc8 12. Qa4 {White creates a potential discovery against 
Black's king.} Qd7 13. cxd6 Ng6 14. Rxg6 {If Black takes the rook with either 
pawn, then play Nxe5.} cxd6 {Black's best move.} 15. Rg1 {Retreat to safetey.} *

