1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 d6 4. d4 Bd7 5. d5 Nce7 6. Bxd7+ Qxd7 7. c4 Nf6 8. 
Nc3 Qg4 9. c5 Qxg2 10. Rg1 Qh3 11. Nb5 Nexd5 {Black tries to give up a knight to 
errode white's center. In the end, he'll have two pawns for the piece, but a 
cramped and passive position.} 12. exd5 Qd7 13. Qb3 {With his potential pawn 
cover on both sides already broken up, white should probably look to trade 
queens soon.} *

