1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 a6 4. Bxc6 dxc6 5. O-O Bc5 {This line is very similar 
to the previous 5...Bc5 variation, but maybe a bit simpler.} 6. Nxe5 Nf6 7. d3 
Be6 8. Nf3 h6 9. a3 O-O 10. Nc3 {Remember, in the Exchange, trade down and keep 
that winning pawn structure!} *

