1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 a6 4. Bxc6 dxc6 5. O-O Bc5 6. Nxe5 Ne7 $4 {6...Ne7 
blunders piece. After the following continuation...} 7. Nxf7 Kxf7 8. Qh5+ Ng6 
{It doesn't matter if white blocks with the g pawn or the knight, or move out of 
the check, our next move is to take the free bishop.} 9. Qxc5 *

